Storefronts in the historic town of Roslyn, along the Snoqualmie pass east of Seattle.
</p>
<p class="en">
    Founded in 1886 as a coal mining company town, Roslyn was the filming location for The Runner Stumbles, Northern Exposure, and The Man in the High Castle. 
</p>

<p class="jp">
<span class="title_jp">西洋の町</span>
シアトルの東にあるスノークォルミー峠沿いにある、歴史ある町ロズリンの店舗。</p>
<p class="jp">

1886年に石炭採掘会社の町として設立されたロズリンは、テレビドラマ『The Runner Stumbles』、『Northern Exposure』、『高い城の男』の撮影地となった。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Pacific Northwest" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Storefronts in the historic town of Roslyn, along the Snoqualmie pass east of Seattle. Founded in 1886 as a coal mining company town, Roslyn was the filming location for The Runner Stumbles, Northern Exposure, and The Man in the High Castle.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2411_A7R09323.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2411_A7R09323.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Golden Ginkgo・黄金色のイチョウ</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241125/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Golden Ginkgo・黄金色のイチョウ" /><published>2024-11-25T00:00:00-08:00</published><updated>2024-11-25T00:00:00-08:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ginko</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241125/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A photo of golden ginkgo leaves at Umeda’s Umekita Park, from a month ago.
</p>

<p class="jp">
1か月前の梅田のウメキタ公園の黄金色に色づいたイチョウの葉の写真。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Osaka" /><category term="Foliage" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A photo of golden ginkgo leaves at Umeda’s Umekita Park, from a month ago.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R07560_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2410_A7R07560_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Monorail</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241122/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Monorail" /><published>2024-11-22T00:00:00-08:00</published><updated>2024-11-22T00:00:00-08:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/monorail</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241122/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
1960s Alweg Monorail still runs in downtown Seattle, with the original cars.
</p>

<p class="jp">
1960年代に建設されたアルウェッグモノレールは、オリジナルの車両を使用して、現在もシアトルのダウンタウンで運行されている。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Pacific Northwest" /><category term="Trains" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[1960s Alweg Monorail still runs in downtown Seattle, with the original cars.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2411_A7R09303_ai_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2411_A7R09303_ai_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">2 Shots 4 Trains・2 写真 4 列車</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241118/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="2 Shots 4 Trains・2 写真 4 列車" /><published>2024-11-18T00:00:00-08:00</published><updated>2024-11-18T00:00:00-08:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ochanomizu</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241118/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
The popular Ochanomizu intersection of multiple train lines, over the Kanda River. This is a two shot composite. From top to bottom: the JR Sobu line, the JR Chuo line, the Tokyo Metro Marunouchi line.
</p>

<p class="jp">
神田川にかかる複数の路線が交差する人気の御茶ノ水駅交差点。これは2枚の写真を合成したものである。上から順に、JR総武線、JR中央線、東京メトロ丸ノ内線。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Tokyo" /><category term="Trains" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The popular Ochanomizu intersection of multiple train lines, over the Kanda River. This is a two shot composite. From top to bottom: the JR Sobu line, the JR Chuo line, the Tokyo Metro Marunouchi line.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2411_A7R09245_ai.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2411_A7R09245_ai.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Light Cycles</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241117/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Light Cycles" /><published>2024-11-17T00:00:00-08:00</published><updated>2024-11-17T00:00:00-08:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/light-cycles</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241117/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
A photo from the Light Cycles event at the Kyoto Botanical Gardens.
</p>

<p class="jp">
京都府立植物園で開催されたライトサイクルズのイベントの写真。
 </p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Lightup" /><category term="Foliage" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A photo from the Light Cycles event at the Kyoto Botanical Gardens.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2411_A7R08900.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2024/2411_A7R08900.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Jimbocho・神保町</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241116/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Jimbocho・神保町" /><published>2024-11-16T00:00:00-08:00</published><updated>2024-11-16T00:00:00-08:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/jinbocho</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/241116/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Tokyo’s Jimbocho district of used bookstores, their vast selection spilling out onto the sidewalks, is a fascinating photographic subject. I spent hours walking around, looking at what they had to offer.
</p>

<p class="jp">
東京の神保町にある古本屋街は、その品揃えが歩道まであふれ出ているという、魅力的な写真の被写体である。私は何時間も歩き回り、彼らが提供しているものを見て回った。
 </p>
